*
 * Base enum class
 * @example
 * const Colors = new Enum(['RED', 'BLACK', 'GREEN', 'WHITE', 'BLUE']);
 *
 * const ANSWER = new Enum({
 *   YES: true,
 *   NO: false,
 *   // Passing functions as values will turn them into getters
 *   // Getter results will appear in ::values
 *   MAYBE: () => !Math.round(Math.random()),
 * });
